{"questionId":"13890","questionHtml":"<p>Find the value&nbsp;of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\"> <mi>r</mi> </math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid approach &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg</em>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4 \\times {r^1} = 36\"> <mn>4</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>r</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msup> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mn>36</mn> </math></span>,&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"4 \\times {9^{n - 1}}\"> <mn>4</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mn>9</mn> <mrow> <mi>n</mi> <mo>−</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> </math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r = 9\"> <mi>r</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>9</mn> </math></span>&nbsp; (accept&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sum\\limits_{k = 0}^m {4 \\times {9^k}} \"> <munderover> <mo movablelimits=\"false\">∑</mo> <mrow> <mi>k</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> <mi>m</mi> </munderover> <mrow> <mn>4</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mn>9</mn> <mi>k</mi> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"m\"> <mi>m</mi> </math></span>&nbsp;may be incorrect) &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;A1 N2</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13890","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ1.S_7b.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of r .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}